Q3Ô∏è‚É£ Read-Only Data Create a class Employee: private empId only getter (no setter) value set using constructor 

Q3Ô∏è‚É£ Read-Only Data

Goal: Value set once, cannot be modified later

class Employee {

    // Step 1: Private variable
    private int empId;

    // Step 2: Constructor initializes value
    Employee(int empId) {
        this.empId = empId;
    }

    // Step 3: Only getter (NO setter)
    public int getEmpId() {
        return empId;
    }
}

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Employee e = new Employee(101);
        System.out.println("Employee ID: " + e.getEmpId());

        // e.empId = 200; ‚ùå not allowed
    }
}


üß† Interview line:

Read-only data is achieved using private variable, constructor, and no setter.
